Class TmlElkDuration

                      Template tml)

        tmlElk - The main template, which will be supplemented by tml. tmlElk is immutable.
        tml - Template to be used to generate Duration ELK log. It's recommended to use TmlDuration implementations.

    • Method Detail

      • create

        public java.lang.String create()
        Creating ELK log with Duration information. For example: 
         
 Template tmlElk = new TmlElkStd(new TmlInfo("Hello, {}!", "log"));

 String actual = new TmlElkDuration(
         tmlElk,
         new TmlDuration(200L)
 ).create();
        Or: 
         
 Template tmlElk = new TmlElkStd(new TmlInfo("Hello, {}!", "log"));
 String actual = new TmlElkDuration(
         new TmlElkThread(
                 tmlElk,
                 new TmlThread()
         ),
         new TmlDuration(200L)
 ).create();
        If tmlElk is null, then tmlElk creating empty JSON object. If tml is null, then the following will be added to the created tmlElk: 
         
 {
   "duration_unit": null,
   "duration_value": null
 }
        Specified by:
        create in interface Template
        Returns:
        ELK log with Duration information.
